Key Match Events: Jamie Leweling scored the only goal of the game, leading Germany to a 1-0 victory over the Netherlands.
Jamie Leweling's initial goal was disallowed for offside by VAR.
Oliver Baumann made two crucial saves to maintain a clean sheet on his debut.
Xavi Simons hit the bar with a shot from 25 yards out.
Donyell Malen's late strike was saved by Oliver Baumann.
Pre-Game Insights: The Allianz Arena honored Germany legends Manuel Neuer, Toni Kroos, Ilkay Gundogan, and Thomas Muller before the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Julian Nagelsmann made five changes to the team, including debutants Oliver Baumann and Jamie Leweling.
Nagelsmann and Germany fans can be excited about the performance of the new-look team, including the contributions of young players like Angelo Stiller and Aleksandar Pavlovic.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The loss means the Netherlands have suffered their first defeat in the league phase of the UEFA Nations League since September 2020.
